{
  "stem": "13524.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My sister and my brother went to Hebrew Gymnasium, so I even had a smattering of Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Today when I go to Israel, my friends who knew me from before the war are amazed how much Hebrew I understand and how much Hebrew I can speak.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that was pleasant.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's correct.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember on the very day that war-- the Germans [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] dropped bombs very close to us, on a bridge on which there were trains going with the soldiers travelling.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I wouldn't know exactly which direction, because by the time I reached the bridge and saw what was happening, it was already-- the bridge-- the train was standing.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a lot of blood and a lot of crying and a lot of dead people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But my mother was a nurse during the First World War.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She took lots of sheets and tried to bandage them and helped them the best she knew how.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And later, it was cordoned off, and we were told to go.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my mother always used to tell me, go home.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I-- we did go home, eventually, and a proper ambulance came to help and to take them away.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But the Germans did a lot of damage on that very first day.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the distance from my home to that bridge was perhaps half a kilometer-- not further than that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we saw the planes-- whoosh-- swooping down on the bridge.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We saw the bombs falling.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Terrified!",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Terrified.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, I sort of-- I always had the attitude to accept these things.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even then, as bad as it was, we accept it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The next thing-- I remember that more planes came the same day, in different spots.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
